metadata.name: Artifact #218
metadata.description:
This project is about uncovering artifacts.

Each piece is determined by approximately 15 parameters. This allows for a multitude of possible forms, and each iteration is an artifact to be discovered within the multidimensional space.

This work is focused around discovery. It is about exploring the space of the algorithm, shedding light on its many forms, and sometimes finding artifacts of the real world embedded within them.

Technically, this work is a composition of three primary elements: Voronoi tessellations, orthographic projection, and the depth-sort algorithm.
The latter of these is integral to the rendering mechanism. It works intuitively, drawing distant objects before near objects, evaluating the distance of each object according to its geometric center. It does this precisely, and in doing so, it can produce interesting visual artifacts, drawing some shapes in an unexpected order.



This has been a fascinating study, bringing light to unreal shapes and forms, and uncovering artifacts in an impossible space.

I hope you enjoy it,
Nat Sarkissian





Technical Notes:
- Append “&mag=N” to the end of the URL in live mode to specify a resolution multiplier. It will render the image N times larger than the size of your window. If you have specified anything greater than 1, a download will start automatically once the rendering is done.

metadata.name: ASSEMBLING MACHINE #174
metadata.description:
The machine never sleeps.
Build. Construct. Develop. Create. Form. Produce. Generate. Repeat.
---------------
Collectors at the highest tier (125 tez) may claim a signed 8”x10” print of their mint. Please look for details about prints on Twitter (@teaboswell), or contact me directly
---------------
CONTROLS:
A - Toggle loading animation (off by default to improve performance)
S - Download image
Double tap (mobile) - Download image
1-6 - Modify scale (1 = default, 2048 x 2730px, 6 = maximum, 12288 x 16380px (very performance intensive, will take a long time to render))
F - Fit to current screen size
G - Toggle grain overlay
L - Toggle background grid lines
B - Cycle border sizes (0 -> 100 -> 200 -> 300px)

You can modify the x and y url parameters to set a custom size. Note that the image will change to fit the new size, but overall drawing style, colors, etc. will remain the same.
(For example, for a 1000x2000 image, add &x=1000&y=2000)

metadata.name: MONOLITH #70
metadata.description:
Very limited facts are known about these strange monolithic structures. Black, rectilinear, similar to obsidian stone but made of strange materials. According to legend, an ancient civilization of high intelligence, called the Explorers of Latent Space, distributed hundreds of monoliths throughout time and space in order to study the behavior of species in the infinite Universe.

Some say that it is the divine intelligence of God. Others say that, in spite of their objectual and material condition, the monoliths possess their own consciousness and an intelligence beyond the natural and artificial. Their purpose or objective, to this day, remains a mystery.

_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_

this work is done only with code, using threejs and p5js
it might be a bit slow on low-end devices, be patient

metadata.name: Agents 2.0 #168
metadata.description:
There are more than thousand agents(random). These agents can move in any direction. I have given 3 types of direction. First is single(together) direction, second is multi(against) direction and the last is "No Movement(Direction)". Agents have their  own speed, size, movement smoothness, and turbulence. The art is programmatically drawn using basic shapes, math, random using p5js.

All the agents walks around 100 to 230 steps. All speed, smoothness, waviness, turbulence, size, direction, color are randomly generated.

In this art, I am using 29 color palettes. these palettes are from: https://ronikaufman.github.io/color_pals/

Press s or 'S' to save image in default quality.
Add scale=print& before fxhash in the URL to save image in high quality.
Add scale=print2& before fxhash in the URL to save image in highest quality.

Example:
Before: https://gateway.fxhash2.xyz/ipfs/QmYiErKegzf66TgVB...../?fxhash=ooXFx4Cbn23Sacb...
After: https://gateway.fxhash2.xyz/ipfs/QmYiErKegzf66TgVB...../?scale=print&fxhash=ooXFx4Cbn23Sacb... 

Note: Art can take some minutes to render.

Art: 8/2/2022
Created By: ArtLife
Twitter: https://twitter.com/iamPraveenIN
